    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.4016/1662a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-26T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 26, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Refer to my telegram April 23, 6 p.m. to Consul General.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d237fn2">Not printed.</note> Press correspondence from Berlin states
                    reports are current that forcible dissolution of B’nai B’rith lodges in Germany
                    were precipitated by a resurgence in the United States of anti-Nazi propaganda
                    as manifested by La Guardia incident.<note n="3" xml:id="d237fn3">See <ref
                            target="#pg_367">pp. 367</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I would like your views and any comment as to the reasons behind this step and
                    whether the attack on cultural and charitable phases marks a new departure in
                    German Government policy. Keep me advised as to developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
